    "body" : "Since you&#39;re cast it to an int, you&#39;ve introduced the year 2038 problem (the equivalent of Y2K for Unix).  That&#39;s when Unix epoch hits 2 billion and rolls over to negative.  The fix is to move to 64-bit Unix.  The Java equivalent is to leave it as a long."
