    "body" : "<p>Avoid the Date object creation w/ <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/System.html#currentTimeMillis()\" rel=\"noreferrer\">System.currentTimeMillis()</a>.  A divide by 1000 gets you to Unix epoch.</p>\n\n<p>As mentioned in a comment, you typically want a primitive long (lower-case-l long) not a boxed object long (capital-L Long) for the unixTime variable's type.</p>\n\n<pre><code>long unixTime = System.currentTimeMillis() / 1000L;\n</code></pre>\n"
