    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java 8 added a new API for working with dates and times. \nWith Java 8 you can use</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.time.Instant\n...\nlong unixTimestamp = Instant.now().getEpochSecond();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>Instant.now()</code> returns an <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/Instant.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Instant</a> that represents the current system time. With <code>getEpochSecond()</code> you get the epoch seconds (unix time) from the <code>Instant</code>.</p>\n"
